            "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
            "ts": "1554146683.000000"
        },
        "client_msg_id": "280ac6c7-ff15-45fa-8355-7dd5a9900326",
        "text": "On <http:\/\/vitor.io\/on-dynamicland>\n\nThere seem to be three distinct goals that tend to get conflated:\n\n1. Seeing as you create.\n2. Seeing what others have created. Or rather, creating in a way that makes creations easy for others to appreciate\/remix\/contribute to.\n3. Keeping a closely-coupled group on a single page about what they are seeing.\n\nAll three directions seem complementary, in that there's no reason they can't steal ideas from each other. The eventual goal seems like a workspace that supports groups spanning a spectrum of sizes (including individuals), and that is easy to export from one group to another.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "6e649a383cf8",
            "image_72": "https:\/\/avatars.slack-edge.com\/2019-07-14\/687915485201_6e649a383cf8f9e366e3_72.png",
            "first_name": "Kartik",
            "real_name": "Kartik Agaram",
            "display_name": "",
            "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
            "name": "ak",
            "is_restricted": false,
            "is_ultra_restricted": false
        },
        "thread_ts": "1554092241.009900",
        "parent_user_id": "UH85W1ML1",
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "4ktD",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "On "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "http:\/\/vitor.io\/on-dynamicland"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\nThere seem to be three distinct goals that tend to get conflated:\n\n1. Seeing as you create.\n2. Seeing what others have created. Or rather, creating in a way that makes creations easy for others to appreciate\/remix\/contribute to.\n3. Keeping a closely-coupled group on a single page about what they are seeing.\n\nAll three directions seem complementary, in that there's no reason they can't steal ideas from each other. The eventual goal seems like a workspace that supports groups spanning a spectrum of sizes (including individuals), and that is easy to export from one group to another."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
