                                "text": "\n\nI think the most difficult thing about Dynamicland is importing a shared vocabulary of a group when you aren't part of the group. It's like the difficulty of understanding the implementation of some large system, but now many times harder.\n\nIt's easy to think this difficulty is comparable to the difficulty of getting to Oakland, or of getting invited into Dynamicland. But I think it's orders of magnitude harder. It's the \"essential complexity\" here.\n\nAs you point out, there are two ways to go about it:\n\na) Emphasize automation first, and try to create a single space with bespoke hardware and software in hopes that it automatically facilitates a wide range of conversations.\n\nb) Emphasize the facilitation, and hope that the variables introduced by the facilitators don't make it too intractable to make generalities about the approach. Then hope that the lessons learned are amenable to automation.\n\nBoth seem hard.\n\n(Thanks for reminding me of this forum. I'd signed up back when it was called tbd.cool.)"
